<br>
Smiling at him ever so slightly, they exchanged vials.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now then, was that all for today?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odyessy7>Odyessy7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/03 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1208.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dreams in the Dark</span><hr size=1> The man with half a soul, looked at the vial of Minru's blood, holding it up as if seeing a rare gem. His face was calm, emotionless, even his eyes seemed barely interested yet he handled the vial carefully. His grey eyes locked onto Minru's for a moment and without saying more than a polite &quot;thank you&quot;, left the building of shadows and dark hearts.<br>
