The feel of steel against her shoulder...<br>
The ungodly pain as the disease entered her body...<br>
<br>
Minru had gone out of the League of Shadows hall on her way to try to make contact with Meledi to gather more information on the state of her brother.  She had not gotten but a couple hundred yards away from the doors of the Shadows, just out of sight of the guards, when two hunters jumped at her.  They had the element of surprise, with one catching her shoulder and scratching her with the disease ridden blade.<br>
<br>
Holding herself up with every ounce of concentration, she turned to face the two, sending her spectral minion against the one that cut her, while draining the life from the other to sustain herself as the painful disease coursed through her body.  Vaguely aware of what was going on around her, she watched as the one that struck her ran with her minion giving chase.  She staggered back to the guildhouse, just in sight of the guards.<br>
<br>
Tears running down her face, she gasped...<br>
<br>
&quot;Katomi, I need you&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysticlioness>MysticLioness</A> at: 12/8/03 11:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=katomishinai>Katomi Shinai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Backstabbing Pox Bringer<br>Kitty Kat!<br>r0xx0r p0xx0r</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/03 12:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1208.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dreams in the Dark ((GORE WARNING!))</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*As she departs the city after a night of training, her blue ears tilt back as she hears a cry...Sniffing at the air, her mouth slightly open, cracked lips breaking anew to allow more blood to come from them in small lines, she tastes the night...Searching...*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Minru!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*Her poxed eyes swirl as she searches the night, her left arm trembling madly as she stumbles out further, sniffing at the air...Skills inherited by her Father live within her plagued blood, aiding her to search...To track...To find.<br>
<br>
It is not long before she sees her...The one who has walked her through much since her own return to the shadows, and she runs over, crashing down upon her own knees crudely, looking over the body of one, watching as Minru gasps in waves of pain...*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Minru...What has...HIM!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*Her eyes widen in near horror, her mind racing as the other scent reaches her nostrils, her plagued body shivering in delight a moment, then thoughts of what is within the one laying before Katomi strikes her senses.*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Come...I cannot watch you here, too many eyes are about...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*She picks up Minru, leaning her own head back and outstretching her trembling arm, mindful no part of herself that is consumed by the plague touches Minru's flesh, wary of the scent she has already picked up from this one. Keeping her as close as she can, she stumbles past the gates, hissing at the guards who try to take what she holds. Seeing the marred form of the plagued Tier`Dal, they back off...The stench alone from the plague warning enough.<br>
<br>
Carrying Minru's increasing weight as the plague takes over her form so unused to such tortures, her blood growing thick, Katomi knows she needs to work quickly and soon...Else Minru will perish. Daring a glance down, she can see the pox working over Minru's eyes...<br>
<br>
Faster! She stumbles faster down corridors, rushing down past the waterfall, hugging Minru tight to her...<br>
<br>
The guards have learned long ago to not keep the bars down as she approaches...The decay and pox heavy upon the air, burning their lungs long before she nears, the gates already being cranked open...Their dread of HIS touch mightier than the fear of the Hatred of the Dark Prince.<br>
<br>
Up over the waters, down and to the left, then a quick right...Minru's body begins to reek of the pox, nothing as strong as that which resides within the Backstabbing Poxbringer, but enough that it should damage Minru permanently if it is not aided quickly.<br>
<br>
Ducking into a seldom visited building, she falls into a wall that is guised for what it truly is...For what Katomi needs to do, she needs cover of silence and noise alike, a place where others seldom tread.<br>
<br>
The air is dank and thick with condensation, and chills come up her spine and that of Minru, who is beginning to be overcome by the shock to her system. Katomi looks up, poxed eyes swirling as the waterfall that hides them roars throughout the dying night. She lays Minru down crudely, searching for the mark...*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Pox upon them...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*She spits beside Minru's head...Steaming poxed blood splattered onto the cold, wet and slimy rocks. Something...Or someone...Has dared to take HIS name in vain and strike down one who has guarded over her for so long...One who is akin, if not by blood but only by name, to the Lord and Master.<br>
<br>
Fabric tears through tiny breaks in the waterfall's angry roar, as she uses her good hand to tear open the robe upon the mark. The wound is ugly to the sight, but to her...It is beautiful beyond belief. It resembles the earlier stages of her own pox, but she knows the stench, she knows what this will do if not properly removed. Her left arm trembling, she takes her stiletto out from it's sheath, steadying her arm with a prayer to HIM, her chewed and bloody tongue rolling over words that only shadowwalkers truly understand.<br>
<br>
As she speaks the incantation, shadows swirl around the blade, unseen by most eyes, steadying the blade. It is with this that she has been able to strike so true in the hunt with her hand in such condition as it is...Her two-fingered-thumbed hand holding the blade in an odd, yet strangely powerful grace, she plunges it down deep, as shadows swirl out and tear open Minru's wound.<br>
<br>
Minru's body arches back and the poxed blood sprays out, the moss-covered rocks being covered in a thin film. Bending down, nearly vampiric in motions, Katomi leans down and bites into the bitter darkened flesh, ignoring the gasping screams of her friend and ally as she begins to take the newfound plague into herself, taking deep draughts of the venomous brew.<br>
<br>
Her own back arches, but snapping sounds as bones crack, the frailty of her own body eminent as one of HIS plagues is passed into her, rushing through her own body, mingling in ways HE had not yet intended. As her arm begins to shake more violently, she tosses down her stiletto, taking deep gasps, her breaths nearly matching Minru's as she continues to lay there, exposed wound bleeding freely.<br>
<br>
Pulling Minru up to her, leaning her own back against the slick walls, she lets out a slight whimper, as the fresh welts upon her back begin to split, burst and bleed anew. She tightens her grip about Minru's form, her plagued arm wrapped about Minru's waist tight as it drips furiously of her own plagued blood. Taking her good hand, she brushes Minru's hair aside and continues the feasting of the poxed blood. Her teeth, long ago sharpened to points, tear more of Minru's flesh, while within the mind of the Poxed One, thoughts concentrate on shadowed words as tendrils come from her, carrying a very deadly plague, mixed with her own blood and that of...Something else. The tips of the shadowed pox drives into Minru's form almost like needles, driving deep as they seek their prize.<br>
<br>
Nails from her plagued hand dig deep into Minru's right side, as the arm continues to shake violently, her grasp deadly, knowing she cannot stop or her friend's life shall be forfit.<br>
<br>
The shadowed pox that drove down moves quickly within the fallen Tier`Dal's body, wracking her in ways seemingly deadly...The plague which HE, HIMSELF infected Katomi with, literally flies through Minru's shivering body, eating away at the plague that she was cut with.<br>
<br>
A scream sounds from this unseen place, sickening to it's very core. Through thousands of miles, the scream can be felt...Not merely heard...Momentarily stunning any shadowwalkers. Any who have ever passed her, smelled the stench of her plague, can feel her now, before the shadows become chilled, stilled...and bring the decay and death scents into the air.<br>
<br>
Katomi's head whips back as a burst of magics fly from her body, her skin tearing as the plague rends her nearly asunder, the dark magics that bind her Mother's blood to give her the form of the Tier`Dal are torn from her, her Half Elven form stretching and cracking as Minru's weight holds fast down upon her.<br>
<br>
Her own eyes open, and thick rivers of blackened ichor from both ends, as she tries to blink away diseased puss, so that she may see...Blinking through the mass, she sees Minru's body has become nearly gray with the pallor of the loss of so much blood...The plague has nearly been removed...But at what cost?<br>
<br>
Her head sinks down again, lapping at raw flesh to break open new vessels, taking draught after draught, her entire body begins to shake, and further blackened veins begin to riddle her own body.<br>
<br>
At one of the longer draughts, Minru's eyes flash open, some of the pale violet colour shining out like amethyst ice, a gasp coming to now parched lips which are nearly the pale colour of frosted spirits.<br>
<br>
Katomi holds still, biting down hard, a bone within Minru's collar splitting open as she draws deep of the final remnants of the plague...When the last drink has been taken, Minru's body falls into her, unusually light.<br>
<br>
Whimpers of pain come from her in the darkness...She MUST save Minru...She MUST keep to the Vows she once spoke to the Lord and Teacher Morgrist as she swore herself to serve, undying, to the League of Shadows, and it's Lord and Master...Gray Hateborn...<br>
<br>
Leaning back down, she swallows hard, letting all of the plague she has manifested and drunk trickle down...She then spits hard, trying to clear her mouth of all of it's remnants. Taking a pained, deep breath, she then bites down hard upon her own right cheek...The side not yet infected by the plague. Her mind spins, her world turns upside down and she bites down again, her mind a whirl of incantations and chants...Dark magics HE has not wished her to know, but somehow, tapped as the new plague rushes through her veins and body.<br>
<br>
Clean blood pours into Minru, bittersweet in the affects it brings to the Half Elf as her body trembles even moreso. Faster, and faster, the incantations fly, the shadowed words driving her clean blood into Minru, Fier`Dal and Tier`Dal alike being infused into the fallen one's body, sending reverberations down through her spine, up into her brain, the synapses nearly exploding as life rushes through her broken form.<br>
<br>
As seconds pass by like hours, more and more of Katomi's untainted blood pumps into Minru, the shadows working deep within her, mending diseased flesh into that of the unmarred Minru's form slowly becoming again something even Dominion couldn't resist...Else he find what brought Minru back to her former self...<br>
<br>
Another cry rings out, and Katomi's body flings back, the seizures of the plagues dancing wildly within her body, mixing, overcoming her as her clean blood weakens in the fight. As her own body is flung back, Minru's rolls to land near the edge of the waterfall, her struck arm dangling within it's ever-flowing downpour. What remains of any diseased blood flows down easily into the waters...The fish within the ponds twitching, then burning...So little of the plague doing so much. Spines begin to come from them, tainted, deadly...Diseased. The foolish Leatherfoot who continuously swims there gasps for air and begins to choke, a mass of bloodied spit pouring from his mouth as he takes a dangerous breath beneath the murky waters.<br>
<br>
Those within the Blind Fish watch in horrified awe...A bartender in training drops a 20 year old red wine that he was to take to To`Biath, as he watches the display of the venomous fish rip into the body of the treacherous Leatherfoot who cries out in the silences of the diseased depths...<br>
<br>
Back behind the waterfall, Minru begins to heal...As another, one who tries to strive for anything that will appease HIM and the Shadows, falls back, the seizures taking full over her now...Black veins offshooting all over her. No more screams come from her, the disease that was to torment Minru now in full effect in Katomi's failing body, a voice that was once sung out against the Light is voiced no longer...<br>
<br>
The stench of the plague quickly consumes the Commongrounds of the Dark City of Neriak...Guards and Guild Masters alike choke for breath from the very being of it...Some, those who worship HIM, nod slightly...Knowing HIS touch well.<br>
<br>
As Minru's body begins to repair and retire into a deep slumber of rest, Katomi's is shaken again as beasts from shadows begin to rise, lifting her violently thrashing body into the very wall itself, mumbling in words no one can understand.<br>
<br>
Minru rolls over, a pained moan escaping her lips from the torments of the eve. Katomi is nowhere to be found, the stench of the plague now only coming from the now poxed waters that border the Neriak Commons.<br>
<br>
Footsteps near...Another approaches.*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><CENTER><TABLE>
