The dead do not tire. <br>
The dead do not waver. <br>
The assasin leapt up onto the branch of a nearby tree, hearing the hiss of the undead abomination below him. The assasin, his skinless lips curled into a smile in the face of his death, leaped onto the skeletal beast. Bone clashed against steel blades. Undead claws raked through skin and into bone. Maggots poured out where blood should have been. The assasin's ribs were cracked and ripped from his body as he still fought...laughing in the face of the skeletal death. His blades carved through bone and magic holding the servant together, but his skills were not enough. <br>
Maggots crawling; flesh tearing; insane laughter of the assasin echoed in the air as he died. The skeleton's bone hands crushing his throat. The maggots crawled up the boney frame and began to devour. The undead servant looked at it's own hand, swarmed with small, white worms eating away, with a form of curious intelligence, as it's body was eaten by the magic of the assasin, by the maggots he had for blood. In the stillness of the moment, bones no longer supported by Minru's magic, turned to dust. The maggots, the life blood of the assasins, faded away as if from a living dream.<br>
<br>
Dreaming in the darkness. Memories or delusions of a life &quot;better lived&quot;? <br>
Honor. <br>
Nobility.<br>
 A light shinning inside, equal to the rays of sunlight falling through yellow and brown leaves. Now a light dimmed and swallowed by inner darkness. The past is just a dream. Sometimes a nightmare for those who know they can never go back.<br>
Morcrin awoke from his sleep in the dread of the underground lair. His grey eyes still seeing the faded memories of a past life. A life he knew existed....but as a fairy tale in the back of his mind. A sad song haunting him. The darkness and night was his life now. So many dead because of him...and he felt nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dreaming again...&quot; said the low, gravely voice of Malga Syn, the troll who should never have existed; could not have existed, yet there he was. Real as any horror who ever lived. A troll who learned the arts of the Necromancer. Not a Shadow Knight but a true Necromancer. <br>
&quot;Is your ..failure...to convince Minru that &quot;We&quot; were the threat, to make her confide in you....distressing you?&quot; The troll smiled with yellow, shark-like teeth. His tone was not too sarcastic. He was far more powerful than Morcrin yet gave the younger Necromancer a small, only a small, measure of respect. Morcrin had the ideas, Malga Syn, Black Vach and Pretty Mary were the power. Although this time, Malga argued about the plan. He considered Morcrin's plan to manipulate Minru, to be too difficult; too involved. Malga preferrred simple plans with the red of blood added in.<br>
 <br>
&quot;...No&quot; Morcrin said simply, his voice low. He neither cared nor could be concerned with anyone's idea of him &quot;failing&quot;. His opinion of himself was all that mattered to him, not other's ideas. The young Necromancer arose and cleaned himself from a nearby waterbowl. When he looked up; water running down his face and long, grey hair; his eyes were distant. &quot;Only dreams...&quot; Morcrin put on the funeral shroud he used as a cloak and hood. &quot;Tell Black Vach that he must hurry and use the blood of Minru to find out more of what she knows. Any link, whether by blood or by association, is a link to be used...&quot;<br>
<br>
Black Vach took the vial of Minru's blood into a ceremonial chamber of bones and cracked, dry, earth walls. Unaware of the poison within the blood of Minru. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odyessy7>Odyessy7</A> at: 12/11/03 1:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysticlioness>MysticLioness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Demon Damsel<br>
