<br>
Dreams come in this fitful state, or perhaps nightmares.  She sees herself standing among the stars, a vast purple rolling horizon ahead of her.  Lightning flashes in the sky and the rain beats hard upon her.  She lives in this dream as a servant of the Plague Lord, wracked in pain.  Boils cover her body, puss flows from her, as the skin begins to crack and bleed.  She hears him calling her name, beckoning her to his side.<br>
<br>
The crack of the bone in her collar brings her back into consciousness; she screams and nearly passes out from the pain.  Colors and images flash and blur in her mind… the darkest black… the comforting arms of death… deep reds… a pool of blood… complete whiteness… a sacrificial altar with her upon it… deep purple… someone, a friend, helping somehow.<br>
<br>
For the slightest moment, there was clarity in the confusion.  Katomi was here.  She was helping… healing her somehow, in ways that did not make sense.  The pain lessens, but the deep sense of coldness remains.  Sleep overtakes her, as she focuses on the sounds of the waterfall.<br>
<br>
Others come to her mind, but whether in a dream or in the flesh, she does not know.  She hears Ezentari’s soft voice asking her not to leave.  She hears Ikatsui speaking of a temple and healing.  There were others too, speaking words of concern, of caring.  People she holds dear to her… they were there with her, if only in her mind.  She hears Kazanti… Megwetch… Mycen… Persephoria… she wants to return to them.  She even hears voices of people she does not know, speaking of finding who did this to her.<br>
<br>
She awakens from the void, weak and trembling, in the temple under the care and protection of the Priests.  She sits up slightly and whispers as they look on.<br>
<br>
&quot;Katomi... where... how... is she?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysticlioness>MysticLioness</A> at: 12/11/03 4:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoriafv>PersephoriaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Malevolence<br>There are two kinds of<br>Pedestrians...<br>the quick and the dead<br>~Magically Malicious~</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/03 6:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1208.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dreams in the Dark </span><hr size=1> The still form of Guard D'Vrinn lie in her arms, his flesh damp as the fever seeps from his pores, the pox struggling to keep him firmly within its diseased grip. How weak he seems, stripped of his armor, his weaponry; shaking like a newborn kit as his poxed eyes flicker into Persephoria's clear amethyst gaze, imploring her to help him. Her fingers dig painfully into the hard muscle of his upper arm as she holds him, for she holds now the very bastard who brought her the false news of her husband's death.<br>
<br>
D'Vrinn's head in her lap, her arm about his shoulders, cradling him as she stares into his young face, wondering who has corrupted him at such an age.. filled his naive mind with dreams of power, prestige, and then, betrayal. She exhales heavily as her fingers find the edge of her gown, parting the folds, seeking out the slit along her thigh. Her fingertips brush against her smooth skin and then onto the hardened leather strap of the sheath which holds her dagger. The very dagger her husband had gifted her with right before his disappearance. As she begins to draw it out, she hears familiar voices carried to her through the hallway.<br>
<br>
Ikatsui.. she was not surprised when his voice reached her ears. He often served alongside her within this very Temple. However, what was Ezentari doing with him? Curious, she moves her hand away from the hilt of her blade, smoothing her gown back into place and lowering the head of the the sickened guard to his pillow. Ignoring his cracked lips parting in a plea to her to ease his pain, she rises from his bedside and starts for the door. She pauses, her hand on the knob and looks back to the dying guard as his body began to twitch, the pox taking stronger hold. She smirks.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I will deal with you later.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Passing through the doorway and out into the hall, she follows the sounds of Ikatsui and Ezentari's voices, leading her deeper into the Temple. She turns a few corners as she finds herself in the wing leading to the High Priests themselves. And then, she can hear the voices no longer. Have they gone? She continues on, searching. As she rounds the last bend, she spies a familiar form upon the dias. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Minru!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Upon closer examination, Persephoria notes that her friend has been prepared for a great healing ritual, no doubt by the Acolytes of the Temple. Her eyes travel along Minru's prone body, taking in the arcane runes placed about her, the ceremonial gown. As her eyes travel upwards along the pleats in the robe, and into the face of the young bone dancer, she sucks her breath in sharply. The pox! HE has done this to her. But why? <br>
<br>
She crosses to Minru swiftly, wrapping her arm around her shoulders in much the same manner as she had so only recently held the traitorous guard. However, there was a difference in the embrace, this one kind, loving, if she could yet be capable of such a thing. She brings her hand to Minru's face, lying it against her cheek for a moment before smoothing back her dark tresses. Noting that Minru is struggling to speak, she leans in closely, bending her head so her soft voice carries easily to her ear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Katomi... where... how... is she?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Oh no.. not Katomi. Closing her eyes, she sighs heavily, trying to comprehend just what was happening to those she cares for a great deal. Minru.. and what had happened to Katomi? Where was she? And, how was she? She does not have the answers, and so she simply frowns, squeezing her hand gently and shaking her head.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I wish I knew, Minru. I wish I knew.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
